#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/rerender-memo-with-default-value.md
M|rules|title: Extract Default Non-primitive Parameter Value from Memoized Component to Constant
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: restores memoization by using a constant for default value
M|rules|tags: rerender, memo, optimization
M|rules|When memoized component has a default value for some non-primitive optional parameter, such as an array, function, or object, calling the component without that parameter results in broken memoization
M|rules|To address this issue, extract the default value into a constant.
M|rules|**Incorrect (`onClick` has different values on every rerender):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|const UserAvatar = memo(function UserAvatar({ onClick = () => {} }: { onClick?: () => void }) {
M|rules|// ...
M|rules|})
M|rules|// Used without optional onClick
M|rules|<UserAvatar />
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (stable default value):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|const NOOP = () => {};
M|rules|const UserAvatar = memo(function UserAvatar({ onClick = NOOP }: { onClick?: () => void }) {
M|rules|// ...
M|rules|})
M|rules|// Used without optional onClick
M|rules|<UserAvatar />
M|rules|```